  "text": "Oct4 begins to express in the early fertilization and gradually reduced along with the increased methylation level in embryonic development [CITATION_1] . 4 Overall methylation patterns within bovine Oct4 gene between germ layers and different ages. EN, endoderm; ME, mesoderm; EC, ectoderm. more linked to transcriptional silencing than the upstream promoter region [CITATION_2] . 11 possible binding transcription factors have been predicted in exon1 (Fig. 5) . Some of them would possibly influence the expression of Oct4 and affect the embryonic development of bovine, such as: PLAG, STAF, CTCF, AP2F and KLFS.",
